{
  "texts": [
    "This enables them to predict perceived sensory qualities even in the absence of full compound identification.",
    "Cost-effectiveness is another key consideration.",
    "Sensory panels involve recurring costs related to recruitment, training, and compensation, particularly for longitudinal studies or consumer testing.",
    "Analytical chemistry approaches require expensive instrumentation, reagents, and trained technicians.",
    "Although AI-based systems may incur high initial setup costs due to sensor fabrication and data annotation, they offer substantial long-term savings."
  ]
}